The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Unions and the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions will form a strike commission on Friday to coordinate Monday’s indefinite strike.
A protest gathering will be held on Saturday, while Monday – the day the final vote on the public health law – will begin unemployment.
This action will certainly cause major difficulties in transport, since railway transit will be completely stopped and workers at the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike until 13:00.
On Friday afternoon, the League Unions will report on the details of their Monday strike to be held jointly with the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions.
It will also constitute the strike committee of the LIGA and the National Trade Union of Machinists that will coordinate the actions on Monday.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday the participating trade unions will be on strike for an indefinite period, if a deal with the government is not reached.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report on the date of the end of the strike initiated.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their call for strike.
Instead, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet and decide on the future.
Based on the National Assembly's Monday agenda, it is also possible that only public health law will be voted at very early hours in the evening, or maybe near midnight.
