According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day until 13 hours the workers of the Collective Transport Company of Budapest, the airports of Budapest from 7 to 9 a.m., will hold a four-hour strike the Unions of LIGA of the Electrical Industry and Thermal Energy, the 2nd Educational Unions and the 2nd Educational Unions called to a strike of Education.
The Hungarian Association of Doctors will take a national strike at alternative times and the Democratic Health and Social Workers’ Union (SDTSSS) which is part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum, will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is that the government withdraw its proposal for public health reform and submit a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new form of pension calculation that will come into force next year.
The third is that they ensure, even before 2010, in the case of advanced pensions the possibility that the occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Trade Union of Rail Workers (SLTF), which is part of the League Trade Unions, do not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the railway side lines and expect another different proposal.
Political Capital[b1]: The Hungarian Guard increases the risk in the country
According to the Risk Analysis Division of the Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed in August this year with the support of the Hungarian Better Movement, has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region from several points of view.
In the company's "warning on risks" it writes: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of ethnic tensions between the Roma and non-Gypsies population of Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic clashes may occur".
The main reason for this is that the Hungarian Guard’s political strategy is likely to be the provocation of an event of this nature,” added the representative of the research institute.
They stated that all this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate of the Roma problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groupings, who were able to base their political strategy on the discrepancies between Gypsies and Hungarians."
This aggravates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they estimate.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, "significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country."
They remind us that: since autumn 2006, the reorganization of the radical and far-right groups in Hungary has received increasing publicity and momentum, and that since the summer of 2007, numerous organizations have been formed in the country that define themselves as "national self-defense associations".
"The common trait of these groupings is that they define themselves as civilian organizations, while openly proclaiming the training of their members for defense - even armed - (civil defense, national defense, defense of public order), referring to the inaptitudes of the police, the army, i.e. the state."
They affirmed: all this happens in accordance with the method that attempts to give a civil presentation to different political aspirations, based on the discontent of society with politics and political parties.
For highlighting the civil and the form of association in the case of these associations not only serves to avoid the legal problems of legal registration, but is at the same time also a political strategy.
According to the analysis, the activity of the Hungarian Guard is a risk factor also from the point of view of neighborhood relations.
“In recent months, in numerous neighboring states they referred to the Hungarian Guard as a potential danger, while the ultra-nationalist political figures of certain neighboring countries want to justify their own anti-Hungary policy with the creation of the Hungarian Guard.
