Furthermore, it expands the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that regulated secondary markets are added to multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with current exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment firms to disclose in the market information on the key aspects of their business profile, exposure to risk and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a record of all operations they perform, to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In his passing by the Congressional Economics Commission, several amendments were incorporated, among which it highlights that securitized debts are considered as a "complex" financial instrument given their high danger to the investor, which has been demonstrated with what has happened with the US high-risk mortgage debt (subprime).
