What insurance is good for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the event of possible accidents, is an important expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, gender, license age, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among others.
Having the car is only the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear of what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is embodied in an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for being liable for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a disaster.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, age of the license, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use to be given to it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that the more likely you are to suffer an accident, the higher the fee to be paid.
That is why both women over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics reflect that they have a lower disaster rate due to their prudence.
Also, taking hands on the counts, companies have come to the conclusion that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will influence the frequency, and thus the likelihood of having some kind of perchance.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
This is why the driver has to study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we expose the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that this, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers you a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 have various drawbacks when contracting insurance at an affordable price, such as the reduced driving experience and the age of the license.
Although the ideal place to be well insured is full-risk insurance, there are other more economical options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for an all-risk franchise, so they get coverage of an all-risk insurance but at a more feasible price.
This kind of agreement would mean that the customer would pay a portion of the claim amount.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the customer brings will be pre-established based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," said Luis Noguera, the top responsible in Spain for First Europa, an online insurance mediator.
Another option is an extended third-party insurance, so that the customer is guaranteed protection against damage caused to third parties, although not against those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A counsel.
If you are under the age of 25 try to be careful and avoid disasters as far as possible, as this will impact on the bonus, which can reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate that the company owns.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on such a base fee.
“Bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its benefit.
If the company has had a good year, it can afford to increase the bonuses,” Noguera said.
After the age of 25, drivers have easier to contract insurance, since the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is best to take a full risk with a franchise.
"Normally, young people cannot make use of the experience previously acquired when it comes to an accident, and even when it comes to driving," said the director in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once past the 'fear of the rookie'.
However, if the client is married but still has no children, it is preferable that he negotiates insurance at all risks, as long as his economic situation allows him to do so, of course.
For their part, marriages with children are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest rate of sins, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be one at all risk with a franchise (which can be 300 euros), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of life of the vehicle.
"They carry out more relaxed driving and have greater purchasing power to afford to take on a larger amount of franchise," Luis Noguera said.
For retirees it is recommended to have an all-risk insurance with a franchise (which is 150 euros), or one to third parties extended when you have a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible disasters, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us according to our personal situation.
