The film is like the German series "Alarm for Cobra 11" without a highway, but in a war situation.
In the example of "The Hunting Party" one can investigate, because there actually never was a good film about the war in the Balkans.
At another time, with another director and with another scriptwriter (Richard Shepard in two charges), the story about the American reporters in the war going to detect a war criminal Serbian named "fox", could probably be a new "Apocalypse Now."
Thus, the stories are surprisingly similar: the small teams go twice to the mountain to do something that the army cannot do and every time it turns out to be a journey of madness.
One reason for "The Hunting Party"'s failure is when we are first introduced to Simon Hunt, whom they don't let him be simply a cynic with heart.
No, the script also foresees a love adventure with a Muslim Bosnian who will be killed later.
Then “The Hunting Party” is far from reality, especially when in the last five minutes reporters with impressive speed achieve what NATO, the CIA and all the headhunters of the world couldn’t achieve for five years, which was to capture the war criminal and leave the Muslim Bosnians for fair revenge.
It’s so bad, that they want to appeal to the international court in The Hague based on crimes against kinematic logic.
